  <thing id="tmDrgnbrn" name="Dragonborn of Bahamut" description="{b}Other Racial Traits{/b}: You lose all other racial traits of your original race, including bonus feats, skill bonuses, attack bonuses, save bonuses, spell-like abilities, and so forth. Two specific instances warrant clarification.\n\n1) If your original race granted you a nonspecific bonus feat (such as the one gained by a human at 1st level), any feat can be lost, so long as it is not a prerequisite for another feat you have.\n\n2) If your original race granted bonus skill points, you should deduct an appropriate amount of skill points from your current skill ranks. The specific skills affected are up to you, but the DM&#146;s input might be required to adjudicate tricky situations (such as multiclass characters who might have purchased ranks of various skills as both class skills and cross-class skills).\n\nThe loss of racial traits might mean you no longer meet the prerequisites for a prestige class, feat, or some other feature. In general, you lose any special ability for which you no longer qualify, and nothing is gained in its place. A couple of exceptions exist.\n\n1) If you no longer qualify for a feat due to the transformation, you lose the feat and immediately select a new feat for which you qualify in its place. You must also replace any feat for which the lost feat was a prerequisite.\n\n2) If you no longer qualify for a prestige class, you lose the benefit of any class features or other special abilities granted by the class. You retain Hit Dice gained from advancing in the class, as well as any improvements to base attack bonus and base save bonuses that the class provided. If you later meet all the prerequisites for the class, you regain the benefits.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: Ordinarily, only a 1st-level character can select certain feats requiring the dragonblood subtype (see Chapter 6). However, upon becoming a dragonborn, you can elect to replace one (and only one) of your existing feats with one of these feats. A character cannot have more than one of these feats. The feat to be replaced cannot be a prerequisite for any prestige class, ability, or other feat." compset="Template" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="tmCON" value="2"/>
    <fieldval field="tmDEX" value="-2"/>
    <usesource source="RoD"/>
    <tag group="TemplHelp" tag="Acquired"/>
    <bootstrap thing="lDraconic"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="fDracAsp"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="stypDragon"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xImmFriPre"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDrgnbrnAC"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="11000">~ You retain your original base land speed, as well as any other modes of movement possessed by your original race. Other racial traits related to speed or movement, such as the dwarf&#146;s ability to move at full speed in medium or heavy armor, are lost.

~You lose all other racial traits of your original race, including bonus feats, skill bonuses, attack bonuses, save bonuses, spell-like abilities, and so forth.

~ disable racial abilities
~   var race as string

  doneif (compare(herofield[tRace].text, &quot;No Race&quot;) = 0)
   var srchxpr as string
   perform hero.findchild[BaseRace].setfocus
~   race = focus.idstring
~   srchxpr = &quot;SpecSource.&quot; &amp; race
   srchxpr = focus.tagids[SpecSource.?,&quot;|&quot;] 
   

   foreach pick in hero from BaseSpec where srchxpr
    perform eachpick.delete[Helper.ShowSpec]
   nexteach

 foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill
  eachpick.field[Penalty].value -= eachpick.field[Bonus].value
 nexteach</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDracAspct" name="Draconic Aspect" description="Bahamut has blessed the dragonborn with aspects combining some of the best attributes of good dragons. Upon completing the Rite of Rebirth, a dragonborn chooses which of the following three aspects to manifest. Once the choice is made, it cannot be changed." compset="ClSpecial">
